difference between powershell and cmd

all the switches and parameters in cmd is different for different command :
$ipconfig/?  : to know more regarding the options for specific command.


powershell:
it has modules and commandlets: 

modules: collections of settings or commandlets 
commandlets: commands that can be used in different modules.
to view different modules you can go to powershell ISC 

parameters::
  required: double bracket options are required . some required param are invisible.
  to view the requied service 
      get-help get-<service>
      get-help get-<parameter> -detailed/-example : for more info.
      get-help get-<parameter> -full : for more technical information.
      get-help get-<parameter> -online : for online help.
        
  















